column4: Hedge fund Voce's nominees elected to Natus board
column5: (This version of the June 22 story corrects paragraph 3 to say Weiss was a nominee and had not previously served on Natus' board)

column4: CORRECTED-Hedge fund Voce's nominees elected to Natus board
column5: June 22 Natus Medical Inc said on Friday its stockholders had elected hedge fund Voce Capital Management's nominees to the company's board  ending a months long proxy fight.

column4: Hometown sweetens takeover bid for Australia's Gateway Lifestyle
column5: Australia's Gateway Lifestyle Group  said on Monday it received a sweetened A$713.8 million ($531 million)  or A$2.35 a share  takeover offer from Hometown Australia Holdings Pty Ltd and Hometown America Communities Limited Partnership.

column4: UPDATE 1-Hometown sweetens takeover bid for Australia's Gateway Lifestyle

column4: GE nearing deal to sell industrial engines unit to Advent: WSJ
column5: General Electric Co  is close to a deal to sell its industrial gas engines business to private equity firm Advent International for $3 billion or more  The Wall Street Journal reported on Sunday  citing people familiar with the matter.

column4: JPMorgan subsidiary to sell Saudi Investment Bank stake for $203 million
column5: DUBAI A subsidiary of JPMorgan Chase & Co  has agreed to sell its minority stake in Saudi Investment Bank  for 759.3 million riyals ($203 million)  Saudi Investment Bank said in a statement on Sunday.

column4: China's HNA to sell stake in 245 Park Avenue to SL Green: WSJ
column5: NEW YORK SL Green Realty Corp.  is buying a stake in the office tower at 245 Park Avenue in New York City from embattled Chinese conglomerate HNA Group [HNAIRC.UL]  according to the Wall Street Journal.
